{"type":"message","id":"8d620cf0","parentId":"4105c2a3","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:21:50.594Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_99962975fcef45af83636ace","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Kurultai Monetization Strategy\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-04  \n**Product:** Multi-Agent Orchestration Framework  \n**Positioning:** \"Kubernetes for AI Agents\"\n\n---\n\n## Value Proposition\n\n**What Kurultai Solves:**\n- Single agents are limited; teams of agents accomplish more\n- Multi-agent coordination is unsolved (shared state, task routing, conflict resolution)\n- No production-ready orchestration framework exists\n- Teams running 2+ agents need coordination infrastructure\n\n**Our Moat:**\n- 6-agent production system (Kublai, Temujin, Mongke, Chagatai, Jochi, Ogedei)\n- Role-specific protocols (Developer, Researcher, Writer, Analyst, Ops, Lead)\n- Hourly reflection + self-improvement engine\n- Neo4j-backed shared state\n- Task-watcher daemon (auto-dispatch)\n- Battle-tested on our own operations\n\n---\n\n## Monetization Models\n\n### Model 1: Open Core (RECOMMENDED)\n\n**Free Tier:**\n- 2 agents max\n- Basic task routing\n- Community support\n- Self-hosted only\n\n**Pro Tier ($99/mo):**\n- Up to 10 agents\n- Full reflection engine\n- Neo4j shared state\n- Priority support\n- Analytics dashboard\n\n**Enterprise Tier ($499/mo):**\n- Unlimited agents\n- Custom agent protocols\n- SSO / RBAC\n- Audit logs\n- SLA support\n- White-label option\n\n**Why This Works:**\n- Free tier drives adoption (developer love)\n- Pro tier captures SMB/teams\n- Enterprise tier for serious deployments\n- Open source = community contributions\n\n**Projected Revenue:**\n| Year | Free | Pro | Enterprise | MRR |\n|------|------|-----|------------|-----|\n| Y1 | 1,000 | 50 | 5 | $7,450 |\n| Y2 | 5,000 | 200 | 20 | $29,800 |\n| Y3 | 20,000 | 800 | 80 | $119,200 |\n\n---\n\n### Model 2: Usage-Based Pricing\n\n**Pricing:**\n- $0.10 per agent-hour\n- $0.01 per task routed\n- $0.001 per reflection cycle\n- Free tier: 100 agent-hours/mo\n\n**Why This Works:**\n- Aligns cost with value\n- Scales with customer success\n- Low barrier to entry\n\n**Risk:**\n- Harder to predict revenue\n- Customers may limit usage to save costs\n\n---\n\n### Model 3: Self-Hosted License\n\n**Pricing:**\n- Community: Free (GPL license)\n- Commercial: $5,000/year (MIT license + support)\n- Enterprise: $25,000/year (custom features + SLA)\n\n**Why This Works:**\n- Enterprises prefer self-hosted for security\n- One-time revenue, low support overhead\n- Clear upgrade path\n\n**Risk:**\n- Lower recurring revenue\n- Piracy risk with open source\n\n---\n\n### Model 4: Managed Service (SaaS)\n\n**Pricing:**\n- Starter: $49/mo (3 agents, shared infra)\n- Team: $199/mo (10 agents, dedicated infra)\n- Enterprise: $999/mo (unlimited, VPC, SLA)\n\n**Why This Works:**\n- Highest margins (70-80%)\n- Recurring revenue\n- Full control over experience\n\n**Risk:**\n- Infrastructure costs\n- Security/compliance burden\n- Competition from cloud providers\n\n---\n\n### Model 5: Professional Services\n\n**Offerings:**\n- **Deployment:** $5,000 one-time (setup + hardening)\n- **Custom Agents:** $10,000-50,000 (role-specific protocols)\n- **Training:** $2,500/day (team workshops)\n- **Managed Retainer:** $5,000/mo (monitoring + optimization)\n\n**Why This Works:**\n- Immediate revenue (no product build)\n- Deep customer relationships\n- Funds product development\n\n**Risk:**\n- Not scalable (trades time for money)\n- Distracts from product focus\n\n---\n\n## Recommended Strategy: Hybrid Model\n\n### Phase 1: Open Source + Services (Months 1-6)\n\n**Goal:** Build adoption, fund development\n\n**Actions:**\n1. Open source Kurultai framework (MIT license)\n2. Offer deployment services ($5K/deployment)\n3. Build case studies with early adopters\n4. Gather feedback, iterate on product\n\n**Revenue Target:** $10K/mo (services)\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2: Managed SaaS Launch (Months 6-12)\n\n**Goal:** Recurring revenue, product-market fit\n\n**Actions:**\n1. Launch Kurultai Cloud (managed service)\n2. Free tier: 2 agents, 100 tasks/mo\n3. Pro tier: $99/mo, 10 agents, unlimited tasks\n4. Enterprise: Custom pricing\n\n**Revenue Target:** $50K/mo (80% SaaS, 20% services)\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3: Enterprise + Ecosystem (Year 2+)\n\n**Goal:** Scale, platform play\n\n**Actions:**\n1. Enterprise features (SSO, RBAC, audit logs)\n2. Agent marketplace (third-party protocols)\n3. Certification program (Kurultai partners)\n4. Annual user conference\n\n**Revenue Target:** $200K/mo (60% SaaS, 25% enterprise, 15% marketplace)\n\n---\n\n## Competitive Positioning\n\n| Competitor | What They Have | What We Have | Our Edge |\n|------------|----------------|--------------|----------|\n| **OpenClaw (single agent)** | One agent, no coordination | 6 agents, orchestrated | Multi-agent > single |\n| **Claude Code** | Single powerful agent | Agent teams with roles | Specialization wins |\n| **Pi Agents** | Basic multi-agent | Production protocols + reflection | Battle-tested |\n| **Custom builds** | One-off solutions | Framework + ecosystem | Faster, cheaper |\n\n---\n\n## Go-To-Market Strategy\n\n### Target Customers\n\n| Segment | Pain Point | Our Solution | Price |\n|---------|------------|--------------|-------|\n| **Dev Teams** | CI/CD, code review automation | Dev agent swarm | $99/mo |\n| **Content Agencies** | Research + writing + editing | Content agent pipeline | $199/mo |\n| **Consultancies** | Client research + reports | Research agent teams | $499/mo |\n| **Enterprises** | Compliance, audit trails | Enterprise Kurultai | Custom |\n\n### Distribution Channels\n\n1. **GitHub** — Open source repo, 240K+ OpenClaw stars to leverage\n2. **ClawHub** — Official skill listing\n3. **Discord** — OpenClaw community (10K+ members)\n4. **Product Hunt** — Launch campaign\n5. **Content Marketing** — \"Building Multi-Agent Systems\" blog series\n6. **Partnerships** — OpenClawd, Clawable.ai (deployment partners)\n\n---\n\n## Financial Projections\n\n### Conservative Scenario\n\n| Year | Customers | ARPU | MRR | ARR |\n|------|-----------|------|-----|-----|\n| Y1 | 100 | $150 | $15K | $180K |\n| Y2 | 500 | $175 | $87.5K | $1.05M |\n| Y3 | 2,000 | $200 | $400K | $4.8M |\n\n### Aggressive Scenario\n\n| Year | Customers | ARPU | MRR | ARR |\n|------|-----------|------|-----|-----|\n| Y1 | 250 | $150 | $37.5K | $450K |\n| Y2 | 1,500 | $175 | $262.5K | $3.15M |\n| Y3 | 8,000 | $200 | $1.6M | $19.2M |\n\n---\n\n## Key Metrics to Track\n\n| Metric | Target | Why It Matters |\n|--------|--------|----------------|\n| **Agent-hours/mo** | 10K+ | Usage = value delivered |\n| **Task success rate** | >95% | Quality indicator |\n| **Churn rate** | <5%/mo | Product-market fit |\n| **NPS** | >50 | Customer satisfaction |\n| **Time-to-value** | <1 hour | Onboarding quality |\n| **Expansion revenue** | >20%/yr | Upsell success |\n\n---\n\n## Risks & Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| **OpenClaw changes API** | Medium | High | Abstract layer, multi-platform support |\n| **Cloud provider copies us** | High | High | First-mover advantage, community loyalty |\n| **Multi-agent is a niche** | Low | High | Expand to single-agent market |\n| **Security incidents** | Medium | High | Security-first design, audits |\n| **Pricing too low** | Medium | Medium | Usage-based upsell, enterprise tier |\n\n---\n\n## Next Steps (30 Days)\n\n1. **Week 1-2:** Package Kurultai as installable framework\n2. **Week 3:** Open source on GitHub (MIT license)\n3. **Week 4:** Launch on Product Hunt + OpenClaw Discord\n4. **Ongoing:** Offer deployment services ($5K/deployment)\n\n**Success Metric:** 10 deployments, 100 GitHub stars, $10K services revenue\n\n---\n\n## Bottom Line\n\n**Kurultai is monetizable because:**\n1. Multi-agent coordination is unsolved (we have production code)\n2. OpenClaw ecosystem is growing (240K+ stars, <3 months old)\n3. Enterprises need agent teams (not single agents)\n4. No direct competitors (we're first to market)\n\n**Recommended path:** Open source → Services → SaaS → Enterprise\n\n**Revenue potential:** $180K ARR (Y1) → $4.8M ARR (Y3)\n\n---\n\n*Strategy document. Ready for execution.*\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772760110585}}
{"type":"message","id":"69959f23","parentId":"8d620cf0","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:21:50.609Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_491e9b18ee7f44ef8b4b647b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"name\": \"parse-for-agents\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Parse for Agents - Agent-optimized media credibility analysis API\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"dev\": \"tsx watch src/index.ts\",\n    \"start\": \"tsx src/index.ts\",\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\",\n    \"test\": \"tsx --test src/**/*.test.ts\"\n  },\n  \"keywords\": [\n    \"agents\",\n    \"media-analysis\",\n    \"credibility\",\n    \"ai\"\n  ],\n  \"author\": \"Kurultai\",\n  \"license\": \"ISC\",\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@hono/node-server\": \"^1.19.11\",\n    \"@x402/core\": \"^2.5.0\",\n    \"@x402/evm\": \"^2.5.0\",\n    \"@x402/hono\": \"^2.5.0\",\n    \"hono\": \"^4.12.5\",\n    \"tsx\": \"^4.21.0\",\n    \"uuid\": \"^13.0.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@types/node\": \"^25.3.3\",\n    \"@types/uuid\": \"^10.0.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.9.3\"\n  }\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772760110602}}
{"type":"message","id":"f8e99794","parentId":"69959f23","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:22:00.368Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I'm getting a clearer picture:\n\n1. **parse-for-agents** is a separate project specifically for agent-optimized API access\n2. It has x402 dependencies installed:\n   - `@x402/core: ^2.5.0`\n   - `@x402/evm: ^2.5.0`\n   - `@x402/hono: ^2.5.0`\n3. There's an `x402.ts` file in the src directory\n\nLet me read the x402.ts file and the main app.ts to understand the implementation status.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Found it! There's a dedicated `parse-for-agents` project with x402 dependencies already installed. Let me check the implementation files."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7d43468d7dda4f94bbf66ca6","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/kublai/projects/parse-for-agents/src/x402.ts"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_142a2d46df244ce1ac26b474","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/kublai/projects/parse-for-agents/src/payment-ledger.ts"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_57ec22a2bfba4c2a90d70946","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/kublai/projects/parse-for-agents/.env.example"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":3123,"output":227,"cacheRead":22336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25686,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772760110609}}
{"type":"message","id":"86347750","parentId":"f8e99794","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:22:00.398Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7d43468d7dda4f94bbf66ca6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { paymentMiddleware, x402ResourceServer } from \"@x402/hono\";\nimport { ExactEvmScheme } from \"@x402/evm/exact/server\";\nimport { HTTPFacilitatorClient } from \"@x402/core/server\";\nimport type { Context, Next } from \"hono\";\n\nconst X402_ENABLED = process.env.X402_ENABLED === \"true\";\nconst WALLET = process.env.X402_PAY_TO_ADDRESS || \"\";\nconst NETWORK = (process.env.X402_NETWORK || \"eip155:8453\") as `${string}:${string}`;\nconst FACILITATOR_URL = process.env.X402_FACILITATOR_URL || \"https://facilitator.x402.org\";\n\n// Pricing table (USDC on Base L2)\nexport const PRICING = {\n  analyze: { quick: \"$0.01\", standard: \"$0.05\", deep: \"$0.15\" },\n  evaluate: \"$0.01\",\n  chat: \"$0.005\",\n} as const;\n\n// Initialize x402 middleware only when enabled and wallet configured\nlet x402MW: ((c: Context, next: Next) => Promise<Response | void>) | null = null;\n\nif (X402_ENABLED && WALLET) {\n  const facilitatorClient = new HTTPFacilitatorClient({ url: FACILITATOR_URL });\n  const resourceServer = new x402ResourceServer(facilitatorClient)\n    .register(NETWORK, new ExactEvmScheme());\n\n  x402MW = paymentMiddleware(\n    {\n      \"POST /v1/analyze\": {\n        accepts: {\n          scheme: \"exact\",\n          price: PRICING.analyze.standard,\n          network: NETWORK,\n          payTo: WALLET,\n        },\n        description: \"Media credibility analysis\",\n      },\n      \"POST /v1/evaluate\": {\n        accepts: {\n          scheme: \"exact\",\n          price: PRICING.evaluate,\n          network: NETWORK,\n          payTo: WALLET,\n        },\n        description: \"Prompt safety and quality evaluation\",\n      },\n      \"POST /v1/chat\": {\n        accepts: {\n          scheme: \"exact\",\n          price: PRICING.chat,\n          network: NETWORK,\n          payTo: WALLET,\n        },\n        description: \"Chat with Parse AI assistant\",\n      },\n    },\n    resourceServer,\n  );\n\n  console.log(`[x402] Payment middleware enabled — wallet: ${WALLET.slice(0, 6)}...${WALLET.slice(-4)}, network: ${NETWORK}`);\n} else if (X402_ENABLED && !WALLET) {\n  console.warn(\"[x402] X402_ENABLED=true but X402_PAY_TO_ADDRESS not set — payments disabled\");\n}\n\n/**\n * Middleware that intercepts x402 payment headers on POST routes.\n * If payment header present → verifies via x402 SDK → sets x402Paid flag → proceeds.\n * If no payment header → passes through to normal API key auth.\n */\nexport function x402Guard() {\n  return async (c: Context, next: Next) => {\n    // Only handle POST requests with payment headers when x402 is active\n    if (c.req.method !== \"POST\" || !x402MW) {\n      await next();\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Check for x402 payment header (protocol uses \"x-payment\")\n    const hasPayment = c.req.header(\"x-payment\");\n    if (hasPayment) {\n      // Route through x402 middleware for verification + settlement\n      return x402MW(c, async () => {\n        // Payment verified — mark context so auth middleware skips API key check\n        c.set(\"x402Paid\", true);\n        await next();\n      });\n    }\n\n    // No payment header — fall through to API key auth\n    await next();\n  };\n}\n\nexport function isX402Enabled(): boolean {\n  return X402_ENABLED && !!WALLET;\n}\n\nexport function getPricingInfo() {\n  return {\n    enabled: isX402Enabled(),\n    currency: \"USDC\",\n    network: NETWORK,\n    payTo: WALLET || \"not_configured\",\n    facilitator: FACILITATOR_URL,\n    endpoints: {\n      \"POST /v1/analyze\": PRICING.analyze,\n      \"POST /v1/evaluate\": PRICING.evaluate,\n      \"POST /v1/chat\": PRICING.chat,\n    },\n    free_endpoints: [\"GET /v1/models\", \"GET /v1/pricing\", \"POST /v1/keys/generate\"],\n    free_tier: {\n      description: \"Generate an API key for limited free access\",\n      url: \"/v1/keys/generate\",\n    },\n    agent_integration: {\n      typescript: 'npm install @x402/fetch — then use wrapFetch(fetch, walletClient)',\n      python: 'pip install x402 — then use wrap_requests(session, wallet)',\n      cli: 'npm install -g @x402/purl — then use purl POST <url>',\n    },\n  };\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772760120387}}
{"type":"message","id":"793477c0","parentId":"86347750","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:22:00.417Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_142a2d46df244ce1ac26b474","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import type { PaymentRecord } from \"./types.js\";\n\n// In-memory payment ledger (bounded, matching existing pattern)\nconst MAX_RECORDS = 1000;\nconst payments: PaymentRecord[] = [];\n\nexport function recordPayment(record: PaymentRecord): void {\n  payments.push(record);\n  if (payments.length > MAX_RECORDS) {\n    payments.splice(0, payments.length - MAX_RECORDS);\n  }\n}\n\nexport function getPaymentStats() {\n  const now = Date.now();\n  const last24h = payments.filter(\n    (p) => now - new Date(p.timestamp).getTime() < 86_400_000,\n  );\n  const lastHour = last24h.filter(\n    (p) => now - new Date(p.timestamp).getTime() < 3_600_000,\n  );\n\n  const totalRevenue = payments.reduce(\n    (sum, p) => sum + parseFloat(p.amount),\n    0,\n  );\n  const revenue24h = last24h.reduce(\n    (sum, p) => sum + parseFloat(p.amount),\n    0,\n  );\n\n  const byEndpoint: Record<string, number> = {};\n  for (const p of payments) {\n    byEndpoint[p.endpoint] = (byEndpoint[p.endpoint] || 0) + 1;\n  }\n\n  const uniquePayers = new Set(payments.map((p) => p.payer)).size;\n\n  return {\n    total_payments: payments.length,\n    total_revenue_usdc: totalRevenue.toFixed(4),\n    payments_24h: last24h.length,\n    revenue_24h_usdc: revenue24h.toFixed(4),\n    payments_last_hour: lastHour.length,\n    unique_payers: uniquePayers,\n    by_endpoint: byEndpoint,\n  };\n}\n\nexport function getRecentPayments(limit = 20): PaymentRecord[] {\n  return payments.slice(-limit).reverse();\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772760120408}}
{"type":"message","id":"d7bfa354","parentId":"793477c0","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:22:00.434Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_57ec22a2bfba4c2a90d70946","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"PORT=3000\nOPENROUTER_API_KEY=your_openrouter_key_here\n\n# x402 Payment Configuration (agent-to-agent USDC payments)\nX402_ENABLED=false\nX402_PAY_TO_ADDRESS=0x_your_base_wallet_address\nX402_FACILITATOR_URL=https://facilitator.x402.org\nX402_NETWORK=eip155:8453\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772760120426}}
{"type":"message","id":"adde0165","parentId":"d7bfa354","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:22:09.741Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me also check the main app.ts to see how x402 is integrated and if there are any tests or if it's been deployed.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Let me also check the main app.ts to see how it's integrated and check the deployment status."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7f31db7849c2457f8ddcd1c5","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/kublai/projects/parse-for-agents/src/app.ts","limit":100}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f261a41db81e4f4aba9ef8f1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/kublai/projects/parse-for-agents && git log --oneline -5 && echo \"---\" && git status --short"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":6563,"output":123,"cacheRead":20672,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27358,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772760120434}}
{"type":"message","id":"75c5a0c4","parentId":"adde0165","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:22:09.778Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7f31db7849c2457f8ddcd1c5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { Hono } from \"hono\";\nimport { cors } from \"hono/cors\";\nimport { v4 as uuidv4 } from \"uuid\";\nimport { stream } from \"hono/streaming\";\nimport { bodyLimit } from \"hono/body-limit\";\nimport { authMiddleware, getDemoKey, createApiKey, listApiKeys, deleteApiKey } from \"./auth.js\";\nimport { startAnalysis, getAnalysis, listAnalyses } from \"./analyzer.js\";\nimport { handleChat, handleChatStream } from \"./chat.js\";\nimport { executePrompt } from \"./executor.js\";\nimport { runEvaluators } from \"./evaluators.js\";\nimport { getAvailableModels } from \"./llm.js\";\nimport { getDashboardHTML } from \"./dashboard.js\";\nimport { x402Guard, getPricingInfo, isX402Enabled } from \"./x402.js\";\nimport { getPaymentStats, getRecentPayments } from \"./payment-ledger.js\";\nimport type { EvaluateRequest, EvaluationResult, AnalyzeRequest, ChatRequest } from \"./types.js\";\n\nexport const app = new Hono();\n\n// In-memory store for evaluation results (bounded)\nconst MAX_EVAL_RESULTS = 500;\nconst evalResults = new Map<string, EvaluationResult>();\n\nfunction evictOldEvals() {\n  if (evalResults.size <= MAX_EVAL_RESULTS) return;\n  const sorted = Array.from(evalResults.entries())\n    .sort((a, b) => new Date(a[1].created_at).getTime() - new Date(b[1].created_at).getTime());\n  const toRemove = sorted.slice(0, evalResults.size - MAX_EVAL_RESULTS);\n  for (const [key] of toRemove) {\n    evalResults.delete(key);\n  }\n}\n\n// Global error handler\napp.onError((err, c) => {\n  if (err instanceof SyntaxError) {\n    return c.json({ error: \"Invalid JSON in request body\" }, 400);\n  }\n  console.error(`[ERROR] ${c.req.method} ${c.req.path}:`, err.message);\n  return c.json({ error: \"Internal server error\" }, 500);\n});\n\n// 404 handler\napp.notFound((c) => {\n  return c.json(\n    { error: \"Not found\", path: c.req.path, method: c.req.method },\n    404\n  );\n});\n\n// CORS for all routes\napp.use(\"/*\", cors());\n\n// Security headers\napp.use(\"/*\", async (c, next) => {\n  await next();\n  c.header(\"X-Content-Type-Options\", \"nosniff\");\n  c.header(\"X-Frame-Options\", \"DENY\");\n  c.header(\"X-XSS-Protection\", \"0\");\n  c.header(\"Referrer-Policy\", \"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\");\n  c.header(\"Permissions-Policy\", \"camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()\");\n});\n\n// Request body size limit (1MB)\napp.use(\"/*\", bodyLimit({ maxSize: 1024 * 1024 }));\n\n// Request logging middleware\napp.use(\"/*\", async (c, next) => {\n  const start = Date.now();\n  await next();\n  const duration = Date.now() - start;\n  console.log(\n    `[${new Date().toISOString()}] ${c.req.method} ${c.req.path} ${c.res.status} ${duration}ms`\n  );\n});\n\n// x402 payment guard — intercepts payment headers on paid POST routes\n// Must run before auth middleware so verified payments bypass API key check\napp.use(\"/v1/analyze\", x402Guard());\napp.use(\"/v1/evaluate\", x402Guard());\napp.use(\"/v1/chat\", x402Guard());\n\n// ==========================================\n// Public routes (no auth)\n// ==========================================\n\n// Root - service info\napp.get(\"/\", (c) =>\n  c.json({\n    service: \"Parse for Agents\",\n    version: \"1.0.0\",\n    description: \"Agent-optimized media credibility analysis API\",\n    docs: \"/docs\",\n    dashboard: \"/dashboard\",\n    setup: {\n      step_1: \"POST /v1/keys/generate to create an API key (no auth needed)\",\n      step_2: \"Use the key as Bearer token for all other endpoints\",\n    },\n    endpoints: {\n      generate_key: \"POST /v1/keys/generate\",\n      analyze: \"POST /v1/analyze\",\n\n[522 more lines in file. Use offset=101 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772760129768}}
